The President of Nigerian University Games Association (NUGA), Prof Stephen Hamafyelto, has said that delegates for the upcoming World University Games in China will be selected from the participants of  NUGA games  2022. Hamafyelto announced this at the opening ceremony of the NUGA games 2022 hosted by University of Lagos (UNILAG). The 12-day event which began March 16 and ends March 27, brings together 14,000 delegates from 75 Nigerian universities.   FA Cup Q-Finals: Chelsea beat Boro 2-0 to reach semi-finals     EPL: Saka’s opener keeps Arsenal stronger on top 4     Chrisland shines at 2022 World School Games   13 sporting activities is expected to hold at eight locations in Lagos including the host institution. Other locations include Yaba College of Technology (YABATECH), National Stadium and Teslim Balogun Stadium, Surulere. UNILAG Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Oluwatoyin Ogundipe, played host to dignitaries including Speaker, House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila; Minister of Youths and Sports Development, Sunday Dare; Deputy Governor of Ogun State, Noimot Salako and Group CEO of GTCO holdings, Segun Agbaje.